<div class="faq-section reveal">

  <div class="faq-category">About E5 Enclave</div>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>What is E5 Enclave?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>E5 Enclave Incorporated is a 501(c)(3) lineage-led think tank — a publication of record, a coordinating institution, and a Coalition of the Willing. We convene Black-led organizations, individual builders, partner institutions, and aligned coalitions to repair, rise, and govern the lineage's future.</p>
      <p>Founded June 30, 2024 in Liberty City, Miami. EIN: 99-3822441. Headquartered at 820 NW 64th Street — inside the community we are building for.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>What does "lineage-led" mean?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>It means the institution is built by and for the descendants of the African diaspora in America — the lineage that bore the weight of chattel slavery and its ongoing structural consequences. Leadership, ownership, governance, and benefit flow to the lineage first.</p>
      <p>Coalition allies strengthen the work. They do not govern it. The center holds.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>What are the Five Pillars?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>E5 Enclave's work is organized across five pillars — each one addressing a structural dimension of the harm and its remedy:</p>
      <p><strong>Economic</strong> — cooperative ownership, Black business development, credit access.<br/>
      <strong>Environmental</strong> — food sovereignty, urban agriculture, the FarmBlock FDI dataset.<br/>
      <strong>Educational</strong> — the McCartney Academy initiative at Charles R. Drew K-8.<br/>
      <strong>Engagement</strong> — the Black Dragons Initiative, media, data, cultural infrastructure.<br/>
      <strong>Emancipated</strong> — Restitution 246, the reparations framework.</p>
      <p>The structure of the harm is the structure of the remedy. <a href="/pillars/">Read the Five Pillars →</a></p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>What is an "enclave economy"?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>An enclave economy is a geographically concentrated community that builds economic systems serving its own members first — circulating wealth, ownership, and institutional power within the community before exporting value outward. <a href="/blog/what-is-an-enclave-economy/">Read the full explainer →</a></p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <div class="faq-category">Programs</div>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>What is Lineage Farms · FarmBlock?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p><a href="/programs/lineage-farms/">Lineage Farms · FarmBlock</a> is E5 Enclave's flagship Environmental program — cooperative urban farming in Liberty City paired with a blockchain-anchored governance layer. Land is community-held. Labor is community-recorded. Distribution is community-governed. The FarmBlock Food Desert Index (FDI) measures food access across 50 U.S. cities. CC0 license. Free to anyone working in food justice.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>What is the McCartney Academy?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>The McCartney Academy is E5 Enclave's educational initiative at Charles R. Drew K-8 in Liberty City — named for Ralph McCartney, Liberty City elder and community steward. It targets the pipeline gap between K-8 and high school that has historically routed Black students in Liberty City away from higher education. The program is in development. <a href="/pillars/educational/">Read more →</a></p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>What is the Black Dragons Initiative?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>The BDI is E5 Enclave's cultural and technological vanguard — producing the BDI Sovereign Dataset (1,855 data points, 8 pillars, CC0), original media, agentic AI infrastructure, and economic activation tools for Black liberation. Not a campaign. The forward edge of the lineage's institutional capacity. <a href="/black-dragons-initiative/">Read more →</a></p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>How do I join a program?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>Each program page names its own application path. The fastest single point of entry is the <a href="/coalition/apply/">Coalition application</a> — note in the message which program(s) you're interested in (McCartney Academy, Lineage Farms · FarmBlock, Block to the Boardroom, BDI). A member of the Council responds personally within five business days.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <div class="faq-category">The Coalition</div>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>How does the Coalition work?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>The Coalition follows a <strong>33/17/50 model</strong>: 33% institutional members (Black-led organizations), 17% individual builders, and 50% reserved for partner institutions and aligned coalitions. Member organizations remain sovereign — E5 coordinates, does not absorb.</p>
      <p>Coalition members gain access to the collective research base, the coordination network, program partnership opportunities, and the institutional record. <a href="/coalition/">Read more about the Coalition →</a></p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>Who can apply to the Coalition?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>Four tracks: <strong>Black-led organizations</strong> aligned with one or more pillars; <strong>individual builders</strong> contributing research, technology, or community capacity; <strong>partner institutions</strong> — universities, foundations, coalitions — that amplify without governing; and <strong>funders</strong> providing institutional support. <a href="/coalition/apply/">Apply here →</a></p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>How do organizations formally partner with E5?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>Black-led organizations apply through the <a href="/coalition/apply/">Coalition application</a>. Partner institutions, foundations, and coalitions reach out via <a href="mailto:contact@e5enclave.com">contact@e5enclave.com</a> — we route to the right desk and respond within five business days.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <div class="faq-category">Giving &amp; Support</div>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>Are donations tax-deductible?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>Yes. E5 Enclave Incorporated is a 501(c)(3) public charitable organization (EIN: 99-3822441). Donations made through our official channels are generally tax-deductible to the extent permitted by law. We issue donation receipts for every contribution. Consult your tax advisor for guidance specific to your situation.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>Can I designate my gift to a specific program?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>Yes. In the checkout notes field, designate your gift to McCartney Academy, Lineage Farms · FarmBlock, Block to the Boardroom, or The Record (research and publication). Undesignated gifts go to the area of greatest need as determined by the Council.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>How does monthly giving work?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>Monthly donors are the backbone of a publication of record. Select "Monthly" on the <a href="/donate/">donate page</a>. Your card is charged on the same date each month. Pause or cancel at any time — no penalty, no questions. Monthly donors receive our annual report and program updates by email.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>Are there other ways to give?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>Yes — stock transfers, donor-advised funds (DAF), wire transfer, and institutional gifts are all welcome. Write <a href="mailto:contact@e5enclave.com">contact@e5enclave.com</a> with "Gift" in the subject line. We respond within two business days. For government and institutional grants, see our <a href="/contracts-grants/">Contracts &amp; Grants</a> page.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <div class="faq-category">Institutional &amp; Press</div>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>How do I get on the press list?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>For interview requests, citations, and substantive coverage: <a href="mailto:press@e5enclave.com">press@e5enclave.com</a>. The full press kit lives at <a href="/press/">/press/</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>Where can I read the founding documents?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>The three founding documents — <em>Parallel Negros</em>, <em>Measure the Wound</em>, and <em>Restitution 246</em> — are published on the Enclave's reading surface and indexed in <a href="/record/">The Record</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details class="faq-item">
    <summary>Is E5 Enclave registered as a federal contractor?</summary>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p>Yes. E5 Enclave Incorporated is registered in SAM.gov and eligible for federal contracts and grants. Our federal identifiers: <strong>UEI: H8NGXEYE2HH8 · CAGE: 07E88 · EIN: 99-3822441</strong>. SAM.gov registration expires August 4, 2026. See our <a href="/contracts-grants/">Contracts &amp; Grants</a> page for full procurement information.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

</div>

